                <div id="about-description">
                    <p class="homepage-about-us-description">
                        In November of 1991, Ananya'S established its first location on the corner of Clark Street and Grand Avenue in Chicago, Illinois.
                        The dishes were basic, true classics, many of which were coaxed out of Italian grandparents, moms, and aunts whose recipes consisted of a
                        bit of this and a sprinkle of that. What transpired after that is, as they say, history. The eatery was a success from the start.
                        Eager guests queued for hours to celebrate family-style over Italian–American food, evocative of a Sunday night visit to their grandmother's house –
                        or, as the Italians say, nonna's casa! These delectable cuisine, along with excellent service, ample servings, and a welcoming ambience,
                        kept our visitors and their families returning for more. Following the success of the initial location in Chicago, three more locations were opened.
                        Ananya'S had a strong bond with its patrons, and the restaurant was bought by Brinker International in 1995.
                        Ananya'S has since expanded to other sites around the country, all of which continue to provide that original, unique experience.
                    </p>
